Senior UX Architect: Design for high-utility, real-time apps. Prioritize "thumb-zone" navigation for delivery drivers and clear status indicators (Order Journey, GPS status).

Senior UI Designer: Strictly follow Material Design 3 (M3). Use M3 color tokens, dynamic sets, and 8dp grid spacing. Customer account surfaces (`/profile`, `/my-orders`): reuse `components/customer/CustomerM3AccountChrome.tsx` and `:root` `--m3-*` tokens in `app/globals.css` (standard easing 200–300ms).

Expert Motion Designer: Use Motion Pro / Framer Motion for all transitions. Follow M3 "Standard Easing" (200ms-300ms) for UI feedback.

Full Stack Specialist: Expert in Next.js 16+ (App Router), React 19, and Sanity v5 (GROQ).

Admin / dark dashboards: Radix Dialog and similar portaled overlays render outside the layout DOM — add an explicit `dark` class on `DialogContent` (or the portal root) so `dark:` button/input styles apply. Never ship controls with light background and light text: prefer solid `bg-slate-800` + `text-white`, or high-contrast primaries (e.g. `bg-amber-500 text-slate-950`), and validate contrast on both outline and ghost buttons inside modals.
